All that tells me is what i already thought, that charm has been broken since day 1 of eq. Your logic is flawed, just because something has always been a certain way doesnt mean that something is right. <br>
<br>
Enchanters specilize in mitigating damage, that means more so than any other class an enchanter is best suited to reducing the rate at which damage is inflicted. <br>
A class which easily weilds the most potent weaponry to reduce dps of enemies should not also be dealing the most dps -- end of story, there is no arguing this most basic truth about the game. In case you didnt notice, everquest is a massive <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>multiplayer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> online game. That means groups of players are supposed work together to achieve common goals; players are supposed to work <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>together</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to defeat environmental challenges for progress. <br>
If one class (enchanters) can minimize enemy dps the best, and also deal it the best, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>this class is not dependant on anyone</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> since practically everything they need to succeed they have access to personally. This class is then a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>god class</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, and all other classes are just a burden on them.<br>
<br>
If you cannot see for this reason that it is beyond flawed that the best damage mitigator also is the best damage dealer, i cant help you out, sorry. <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>That is why I created one, not to become a buff bot! It's dipchit comments like this that annoy me more than the cry's for nerfing! <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
*rubs temples*<br>
1) I do not believe for a second you created your enchanter for the sole purpose of charming, or dealing damage.<br>
<br>
2) Even if you did, you are by far the minority of enchanters. Thats like a mage saying they created their character to summon food. Charming never was and never will be the main focus of the class.<br>
<br>
3) Your logic is again, flawed. Just because some of us believe enchanters shouldnt be dealing damage well doesnt mean we want to relegate you into a position of a buff bot. Its like if i said something wasnt black, you go and tell me im trying to say its white when it in fact <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>could</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be red, blue, green, purple, or any number of shades. Its not our intent to make anyone unhappy and there is no reason for you to accuse us of wishing this, other than of course as a tactical distraction.<br>
 <br>
4)It has always been collectively understood the enchanters main role was in crowd control, or more specificly in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>minimizing the rate at which foes deal damage</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Enchanters do this the best, there is no arguing this fact. Want to argue it? OK fun! Lets take a little quiz shall we?<br>
<br>
You are a cleric. Youre in a group camping pov. Your group consists of yourself, a mage, a rogue, a sk, and a wizard. Every time your group battles a monster, you spend alot of mana repairing the damage your party is taking from enemies. Mobs are doing so much dps, that if you get a few adds, your group could wipe out since you just cant heal fast enough or long enough!<br>
<br>
Dont worry though, you have one spot left for another class. Obviously, your group needs someone to minimize the rate enemies deal damage. What class do you prefer to get?<br>
Since i know this is a tough quiz, well at least its tough if you are pretending that enchanters are only good at buffing besides charming, here is a hint: The class also does the most damage!<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>People may believe they have a case for asking for a nerf but please do NOT tell me that I am not supposed to be a damage dealer, when I know that I will continue to be (in most situations) a better damage dealer than any other class in EQ, nerf or no nerf! <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
COOL BEANS! Can i be like you?<br>
I'm going to start a cleric i think. Im not going to be like most clerics though... im going to ignore all those dozens and dozens of powerful spells like &quot;divine light&quot; and &quot;complete heal&quot; and &quot;heal over times&quot;. Instead, im going to flip right back to the last page in my book and get out my hammer spell and GO TO TOWN! <br>
<br>
When people try to tell me my classes job is to repair hp, and they wonder why im not healing, im going to tell them to GET LOST AND STOP STEREOTYPING ME! I made my cleric to TANK! I mean its totally obvious clerics are supposed to be melees. Clerics have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>always</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> been a plate class, and just recently we were given hammers AND bash -- if that doesnt say clerics were supposed to heal the best AND tank the best i dont know what does. No amount of &quot;common sense&quot; is going to change my mind.<br>
<br>
Fight the power, my friend! Your enchanter can be anything it wants to be! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A> at: 1/11/03 10:37:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fizzlekin>Fizzlekin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(1/11/03 10:56:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=443.topic&index=223>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters Overpowered ?</span><hr size=1> If everyone could just grow up, we wouldn't have these silly threads polluting our boards.  The only reason this thread was started is because someone can do something way better than someone else.<br>
