<br>
It is true that no class should be all around amazing.  Yet, you cannot make a judgement call on what a class is supposed to do.  Things like that change so much, and idiocy like that is exactly what was used against mages after our roles changed to rod whores.  It is amazing how quickly you forget what has happened to our class in the past.<br>
<br>
Enchanters never meant to use charm for good, consistent dps?  Who is to say that stun, root, haste, ac buffs, etc were not meant as aids to charm?  You make that call now because its convient for you, though it is not really for you to say.  As for no one making enchanters to charm..I know when I started playing that I played an enchanter alongside my mage a bit solely for charm..and I know others that have too. <br>
<br>
Furthermore, as has been stated, enchanters have been charming since the dawn of time.  It is rather sad that some of you are just now catching on to this.  Though, it shouldn't be too big a surpise... people are generally too ignorant to see something before someone a bit more observant points it out to them.  Nice job only seeing it after a few years, you are right on cue!  <br>
<br>
Some of you are so vindictive, childish and short sighted its amazing.  Yes, perhaps there is a problem with charm, perhaps, but the way some of you sound is wholely sad.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   &quot;If enchanters can have an ability they always have, I want slow, kei, etc..!!!!&quot;  Come on, lets be serious here.  This is a statement reserved for people 6 and under, so unless you fit that bill...lets not use it again.<br>
<br>
Now, there is absolutely nothing wrong with the charm line itself.  If any problem exists, it is the way mobs scale up and the power they got in pop.  Handicapping charm so it cannot be used is no more acceptable then mages not being able to use pets.  The only viable solution I can see that would keep some of you .........people... happy and not totally ruin it would be to make it so charmed mobs have a max hit cap..something along the lines of &quot;Wake the Dead&quot; except not quite as gimpy.  I believe that has been suggested before, and it is the only remotely decent thing offered up as something resembling a real idea.  <br>
<br>
Finally, its quite sickening how some of you throw around the word balance only when its convient and never when it is going to hurt you.  This campaign to keep enchanters balanced within roles and skills should be equally leveled against our own class if you truly care about balance.  Though our charm and mez are ,perhaps, not overpowering, someone who cares so much about balance within roles and skills would also have to demand the removal of these two from our line up.  I remember when we first saw them.. &quot;Oh, I don't think we should get them, but its nice so I want it.&quot;  Yes, some of you have conceded that if charm is nerfed you could accept ours being nerfed too, but with the fervor that you are showing against enchanters, you should be willing to accept nothing less then the total removal of the spells.  <br>
<br>
Oh, and lets not forget mages asking for slow now..and christ someone even mentioned 75%.  Welcome to the wonderful world of hypocrisy.  &quot;Hi, enchanters cannot be the best at mitigating and doing damage, but hell I sure want to be!&quot;  Bleh, whatever.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skidogg>SkiDogg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#333333>(1/11/03 11:41:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=443.topic&index=226>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters Overpowered ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And where the heck did you read that? Enchanters played correctly ALWAYS have been the primary damage dealers bar none since day one of EQ. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  ...<br>
