<br>
in the current situation Enchanters do face danger and many deaths, even though their endeavors are fruitful for te most part.  Necros on the other hand, pre-nerf, with no expansions did everything WITHOUT any danger at all.  Level 50 Necro soloing the king with crappy gear, I think that was WAY worse than enchanters doing a bit of soloing now in PoP.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion though, and we all know what opinions are like.<br>
<br>
Fizz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1557<br> <font color=#333333>(1/12/03 4:56:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=443.topic&index=240>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sebminas.com/eq/baby.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters Overpowered ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Actually we are probably second best, behind shamen, but granted that is arguable if you are talking about a multi pull situation. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Actually, its really not arguable if you look at the spell lists. Enchanters are simply much better than shaman at mitigating damage, even in a non multi-pull situation.<br>
<br>
Enchanters have:<br>
-single target fixed duration stuns (mez)<br>
-ae fixed duration stuns (mez)<br>
-single target stuns<br>
-pbae stuns<br>
-rune shields<br>
-root<br>
-fear<br>
-blind<br>
-slow a negligable % less efficient than a shaman<br>
<br>
Shaman have:<br>
-slow negligable % better than enchanters<br>
-root<br>
-blind<br>
<br>
Even though shaman slow is a little better, an enchanter can make up for that difference through stuns (to mitigate damage imediately), and mez spells (to mitigate more damage over time -- tell me that youve ever been in a group without at least <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>one</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> add?)<br>
<br>
Enchanters are clearly the class you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>want</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to be in your group if mobs are doing alot of damage. Shaman are definately second best, but an enchanter is alot better. <br>
<br>
Besides, even if you were right, and even if shaman were a little better at mitigating damage -- whats your point? Shaman dps is pretty horrible. In long duration fights, if they expend <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>all</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mana <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>and</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> time resources on dealing damage, they might be able to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>compete</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with some more offensive oriented classes. <br>
But surely you can see the difference between 120 dps from a shaman chronically cannibilizing, spending all his time to dealing damage, and an enchanter who can with ease routinely outdamage <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>several</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> rogues, while still being free to do other things (cc, buffs, ect)? Even if shaman were a small percentage better than enchanters at mitigating damage (though i disagree), the fact that enchanters have 10 times their damage dealing ability proves there is a serious balance problem. <br>
<br>
You know, when most people think of powerful classes, shaman is usually really high on the list. The fact enchanters make shaman look underpowered says alot dont you think?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Not quite true, I need heals (lots), I need rezzes (lots), to be able to fight anywhere I wish to have fun I need at least one other pet class, and preferably two (for summoning mobs) so all of a sudden I need a 4 or 5 man group.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I assume by pet class you mean charm class. The fact that you can so easily keep a mob as an ally that you now refer to other charmers and yourself as a &quot;pet class&quot; only proves what we have been saying, the &quot;risk&quot; associated with charm is highly over rated and the reward completely overwhelms it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>That is utter bullshit and you know it! I know we are never going to agree on this but Charm is an enchanters core ability, alongside damage mitigation, much like mages pets and nukes. Removing our charm would be akin to removing your nukes.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Ok, ill just take your word for it and believe that you made your enchanter primarily to charm and deal damage.<br>
<br>
See, damage mitigation, and damage dealing, are polar opposite abilities. Never should one class be able to do both as well as enchanter can, at the same time. Now if a class has to comit themselves to either or, but do neither really the best even with full comitment, thats not so bad (such as in the case of a bard, or a shaman). <br>
That is why your comparison to a mage is flawed. Nuking and summoned pets are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>harmonious</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> abilities - they both are damage dealing. That is why we are able to do both at the same time. <br>
Damage mitigation and damage dealing however is like the equivilant of giving a warrior the ability to instant cast ch himself. Its just ridiculously overpowered. <br>
<br>
Either enchanters must give up some of their abilities to mitigate damage or some of their abilities to deal damage. Keeping both as they are is just not a realistic possiblity if you care about game balance even a little bit. <br>
The reason i and many others lean towards keeping an enchanters abilities to mitigate damage is, because it seems that is closer to their intended niche in the game. Of an enchanters spells the overwhelming majority are supportive in nature, slows, stuns, debuffs, buffs, ect. <br>
<br>
It appears that potent damage dealing seems to be largely an untinended side effect of wreckless design of the charm line. More than likely, charm was supposed to be situational, and that it was never intended for enchanters to keep mobs as pets.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Wrong! Crowd control is one of our main roles, besides charm in many zones is often one of the only form's of crowd control! ie, unmezzable/unrootable mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is what i feel the real purpose of charm is -- to add a little temporary damage to your party, and to cc mobs who cant be cced through traditional means. Like, when fighting giant mobs or if your party isnt assisting, or if you could really use some extra quick dps, that sort of thing. Thats why its an enchanters ability, since it is more than likely intended to be a tool to reduce dps primarily, while offering <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>temporary</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> dps for your party.<br>
<br>
Lets be honest, if it really was intended to be a big dps tool why was it given to enchanters? Why not primarily to mages, wizard, necromancers, or druids, all classes who are signifigantly less oriented in support?<br>
<br>
The fact you also recognize charm as a crowd control tool offers proof this was the main, or at least a major intent of the spell line.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Talk about flawed logic! You would be laughed at and rightly so. The difference here is that clerics are not tanks, were never meant to be and are unlikey ever to be. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
As obvious as it is to you that a cleric is created to heal and not tank, it is equally as obvious to everyone else that an enchanter was created to mitigate damage and not be a damage dealer.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
On the other hand enchanters are THE best damage dealers in the game and one of the best damage mitigators. EQ gives us the tools to do both. NB. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Again, like i said in my first post, just because something is a certain way <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>doesnt</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> mean it was intended, and/or it doesnt mean its right. <br>
<br>
A few decades ago in some places in this country, blacks werent allowed to use the same rest rooms as white people. If you went into these areas and asked white people if it was right, they would probably shrug their sholders and say &quot;yes&quot; and/or &quot;thats the way its always been&quot;. In hindsight, we can clearly see this was not right, and not fair.<br>
<br>
You say charm is intended as a tool to do hundreds of dps from for an enchanter, fairly permenantly, and you also &quot;believe&quot; verant intended this. Well then, either the designer of the spell was severely retarded to implement something so unbalancing, or charm was/is poorly designed. <br>
Given sony/vis track record im going to say the latter (although retardation would explain alot :P)<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I am not stating that this is right or fair but it is the reason I play an enchanter.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
So after all this rambling, i find your real intentions. You dont care if its fair, you dont care about balance, nor are you really comenting on this. <br>
You just enjoy being able to do the only two functions which are needed in eq, pretty much the best. You resent people trying to &quot;nerf&quot; your god class. Grats on being honest, but your arguements credibility just pretty much took a nose dive (if it ever had any in the first place). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A> at: 1/12/03 5:16:41 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=181&stop=200>10</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=201&stop=220>11</a> <b>12</b> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=443.topic&start=241&s